eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 10 Years
Maximum age: 100 Years
At least 15 unstained slides or at least 1 tissue blocks must be collected from at least one prior surgery; frozen tissue is also requested if available
History of transformation of indolent disease to DLBCL
No known bleeding diathesis or coagulopathy
Serum glutamate pyruvate transaminase (SGPT) (alanine aminotransferase [ALT]) =< 135 U/L; for the purpose of this study, the ULN for SGPT is 45 U/L

Relapsed or refractory (resistant) disease, as defined by standard criteria:
* Relapsed: bone marrow blasts >= 5%; reappearance of blasts in the blood; development of extramedullary disease
* Refractory (resistant): failure to achieve CR or CRi in patients who survive >= 7 days following completion of initial treatment, with evidence of persistent leukemia by blood and/or bone marrow examination

groups.description: Participants undergo FDG-labeled standard PET/CT scan followed by FDG-labeled 4D respiratory-gated PET/CT scan at baseline and at 4-8 weeks after completion of radiation therapy.

outcome_measures.measure: Frequency and severity of toxicity incidents assessed by Common Terminology Criteria version 2.0

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will be based on recorded adverse events, physical examinations, and clinical laboratory assessments.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of adverse events evaluated using the National Cancer Institute Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events, version 4.0
outcome_measures.time_frame: Up to 30 days after last dose

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Estimated with exact 95% confidence intervals. Summarized by gender and race/ethnicity using descriptive statistics.
The area under the curve (AUC0→infinity), half-life (t 1/2), and maximum concentration (Cmax) for everolimus will be determined by noncompartmental analysis.
outcome_measures.measure: Pharmacokinetic profile of daily everolimus among patients with PEG tubes
outcome_measures.time_frame: Day 8 prior to everolimus and cisplatin dose
